wikipedia_page.main: Charles Greenway (1862 – 19 March 1949) was an English cricketer. He played for Gloucestershire between 1890 and 1891.

response: Charles Greenway, 1st Baron Greenway (13 June 1857 – 17 December 1934), known as Sir Charles Greenway, 1st Baronet, from 1919 to 1927, was a British businessman.
